<h1>IAAR PART 1946—QUALITY ASSURANCE</h1>
<hr size="2" width="80%"><ul><li><a href="1946.html" name="LOC_P6_214">Subpart 1946.7—Warranties</a></li>

  <ul><li><a href="1946.html" name="LOC_P7_241">1946.704&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Authority for use of warranties.</a></li></ul></ul><hr size="2" width="80%"><!-- TRANSIT - TEXTBAR --><p><a name="P0_0"></a><b>PART 1946—QUALITY ASSURANCE</b></p>

<p><b>Section Contents</b></p>

<p align="center"><b>Subpart 1946.7—Warranties</b></p>

<p><br>
1946.704&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Authority for use of warranties.<br></p>

<p><b>Authority:</b> &nbsp;&nbsp;40 U.S.C. 486(c). </p>

<p><b>Source:</b> &nbsp;&nbsp;50 FR 13212, Apr. 3, 1985, unless otherwise noted. </p>

<p><a name="P6_214"></a><b>Subpart 1946.7—Warranties</b></p>

<p><a name="P7_241"></a><b>1946.704&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Authority for use of warranties.</b></p>

<p> (a) The procurement request initiator is responsible for preparing a written recommendation for those purchases deemed to be appropriate for application of warranty provisions. The recommendation shall state why a warranty is appropriate by specifically addressing the criteria set forth in <font color="#0000ff"><u><!-- TRANSIT - HYPERLINK --><!-- .../Far/FAR46.doc#b46703. --><a href="../../far2afmcfars/fardfars/Far/46.html">FAR 46.703</a></u></font>. The recommendation shall also identify the specific parts, subassemblies, assemblies, systems, or contract line items to which a warranty should apply. </p>

<p>(b) Prior to solicitation of the requirement, the contracting officer shall make a written determination when a warranty provision is to be included.</p>
